Green Tea... You are Green Tea! Strong and very smart you prefer peace to violence
and very rarely take action if it involves
confrontation. But you make up for this with
your keen insight and understanding of the
world and people around you, you have a very
mysterious nature. Many people see you as laid
back and that may be true but you are very
intelligent and make good decisions.

What type of Tea are you? {-With Anime Pictures!-}
brought to you by Quizilla

Your element is Water: Understanding, intelligent,
quiet and calm. You know who you are and no one
can change that. Usually quiet but only because
your listening, don't let anyone think you
haven't got an opinion! Your not quiet because
your shy or sad, your usually quiet because
your thinking. Your answers are well planned
and helpful so people generally seek your
advice. Your the perfect balance between
solitary and outgoing. But sometimes you need a
little time to yourself to sort out your
emotions and figure things out. You understand
the phrase 'sticks and stone' and rarely let
things get to you, whats that important for you
to have to get so upset over? You know what you
want out of life but are simply taking your
time and enjoying things. To you your life is
fine as it is, you can always change things
later if your not happy.

.:-|What is your true element?|-:. -With Anime Pictures and detailed answers-
brought to you by Quizilla
Wtf! bought the vcd of Snow Angel, in the end one episode is missing...^%$$@%!!! esp tt episode is the important one and i miss it the previous time....kns~

How do I put it? 

I just feel tt, no matter how one person is busy with work, it shoulden let it affect its personal life too much. When things cross the border, should try to coordinate with one another and compromise each other. Esp relationship. 

hmm...if one woulden soften the attitude and to make a change for one party, i do suspect that love dosent exist in between. It is not "lose face" to change for one another, but showing how much you care about the other party and willing to sacrifice.

Sometimes, it might be a blessing to find out that someone is standing by your side to share your burden, sorrows and support you all the way thru the difficult times. But it is however, more xing fu to share not only downturns but also the fruit of the labour.

One should try to understand the situation of one another. Dun regret when decision is made and forgotten abt the happiness the time your share and went thru. Forsaking the past and what has built up over the time for something when you just started to haf the taste of some sweetness...wortH?
Im in the office rite now...hehe..juz wanna leave down a evidence that im slacking...keke..actually it isnt slacking either...is lunchtime now mahz...so...boring...

Aw...

I find myself with lots and lotsa emails (including the junk ones) to clear every now and then. That belongs to the company.
I find myself with over limit of usage with my mailbox and have no time to clear. That is my own personal ones.

I find myself tackling with the company's photocopying machines and phones more than the phone and computer in my house.
I find myself dining with colleagues more often than dine in with those that I care. 

I find myself talking to strangers more than the ones that I noe.
I find myself energetic @ my workplace but sloppy and tired back home.

I find myself gaining and losing @ the same time.
I find myself.....not lost but confused.

yeay, after searching high n low, after pending for so long, @ least i got myself a stable job...for 3 mthx. hehe..well is really better than nothing isnt it? i hope i really can stay on this job and persist for 3mthx...is not a joke or sumtink i work for fun now..is serious!!! argh~~~~<scared>

Someone ask me to write down the shopping mood of yesterday...
Ok, places we shopped: Bugis, Suntec and Marina Square
Went to Esprit in Bugis bought a bag and a small pouch(for dardar) @ 50%(staff discount).
next went to suntec saw a fren there working @ U2 as trainee shop manager...wah...1500/mth for trainee lehx...but on probation for 1 yr and long working hours..which make me wonder...wad kinda job do I really want? Ok out of point...
So, we spent time in U2 trying out some shirts and skirts...but i din get anything, instead I bought 2 shirts for him @ $49 hehe...the shirts have very nice color esp the blue...i dun mind spenting some money on him wearing sumtink i like..keke..
after that we went to marina sq to shop @ G2000. Girls and guys if u are very keen on getting some formal attire, u surely woulden want to miss out G2000. They are having 30-50% sale for most of the attire..I bought a cardigan @ 40%. Try alot of shirts and skirts but din get any...haa...coz he wanna buy it for me..
Quite tired walking around, shopping around but still cant get enough of it..hee..

Sorrry action pack lovers...spiddey is going to be emotion on this episode...
well, this movie is really hot. Cant get a proper place @ Plaza Singapura even thou they had 2 theatre showing 1 show @ same time. 
Anyway, 30% action and 70% emotion. JUggling between to be or not to be (a spiderman) qn. oh and M.J, sexy babe...keke...
However, Spiderman needs to find sum other bad guy.. i wish...coz i dun really wanna c his gd fren fighting against him AGAIN~ 1st his father den his son...hmm...
no matter wad, spiderman 3 is definately coming back on nxt yr may...watch out 4 it!

Working has been damm tiring...esp today when OT is required~
OT!!!! argh~ that is damm sianz...didnt haf the chance to eat dinner after 6 but onli haf to work work work until 9...n reach home @ 10 to haf dinner...
Thou, the job is not tough...but the moment when the eyes are in contact with the numbers and computer...haiz...
But anyway...few more days for me.....way to go~!!

WAh Lao! damm tired today sia...walk until my leg so suan (step on lemon lehx)~~~
Just now i went to the book fair and the food fair...
Stroll 2hrs inside the book fair and manage to buy 2 books. 
Xu Zhi Mo de shi & di yi ci de qin mi jie chu (in simplified and red in cover..those who read this bk b4 shld noe the blue color 1...well i bought the red color and small in width coz cheap mahz...onli $5.38..keke...somemore got 10% discount...wu hua hor...)
Den total i spent like $12 plus after discount...anyway Pi Zi Cai got new book lo~!!! weiyen...not the ye mei gui...can go kino c le...but kino ex by $3 book fair selling @ $14.30...wanted 2 buy..but feel my pocket crying...-_-~

After tt, we went to the food fair..crowded but den not too unbearable...
1st thing we ate is the tofu dessert~~weiting, ur fav lehx!!!! I bought 2 @ $1..cheap sia...NTUC sell $1 plus for 1 onli if i rem...den i ate the mango favour and my dar dar ate the original 1..he say original 1 better~
2nd thing is the black pepper satay...10 for $3.90. By right consider quite cheap liaoz...coz $0.39 4 each satay den cum wif 2 rice and cucumber...but then it wasnt tt tasty lehx...we bought 5 chicken and 5 ostrich...

Den on the way, saw alot of pple holding the shark fin dunno wad...wanted 2 try but dar dar say not nice coz his mother bought 4 him yesterday...so i orhx...suddenly i saw the stall jumboo seafood rest...den i so excited coz i work part time there b4...keke...they selling the chilli crab wif fried bun...is i always wanted to eat 1 lo...ping shi serve pple..now finally i can eat!!! but dar dar say he wanna buy the ou ah mee sua...say later we buy these 2 as dinner...go walk walk 1st...

Continue wif the journey, i drank $1 mango juice...the boss very cute ahz..still offer me 1 small cup of lime juice to sample...wah lao....i taste le..immediately react to it...is damm SUAN lo!!!! coz nv add ice den is directly frm the lime 1....diaoz...now i typing i oso feel my saliva savouring...=P on the way, we nv buy any food 2 eat le...coz we bz sampling all the stalls tt provide food sample...

Machiam we're the food sampler like tt...keke..in the end, wah lao..can feel the stomach dam full...coz eat here eat there..drink here drink thr (hai wo go home i LaoSai...) den we bought the fried bun and mee sua...and i bought 3 packet of mee goreng 4 my mother (@ $1 per packet...dam cheap...each packet got 5 pack of mee goreng lehx...) and 1 box of ya juan (duck wrapping?) @ $2....

actually hor..quite xin tiam lehx....coz spent alot le 2day....-_-~ boohoo...
lucky dar dar drive me home..if not actually my barang barang quite heavy sia...
hehe...quite moody this few days...2day go out @ least feel better now...hehe...

Went to catch this movie on its 1st day of showing @ cineleisure. It was a crowd man...the show is quite nice and the effect is gd. 
I can really feel the coldness when the whole New York city been frozen up (or maybe it was the air-con in the theatre? hmmm....)

This show really set people to think. We like to take everything for granted and there will be a time to pay up. 

Anyway some scenes of the show appeared to be in my dream back last few years. I dreamt of 3 tyhoons appear right in front of my living room window and there is lotsa water flooding up. I live on the 10th flr, and imagine the water level rose up so high....*ahem* awesome...
N then right here in the show, there appear exactly 3 tyhoons as well and city was flooded by huge rainstorm. 
Hmmm.....
Deja vu?

Everything has come to the end...the closing of my poly life.
After the exam paper, i dun haf the sense of happiness that i shld haf and i dunno y.
Perhaps it was the feeling of separation that entangle my emotions. argh~~~
Feel damm weak when it cums to this point of time. 
But then again, we still went out have lunch and ktv @ chinatown. 
We werent actually in the ktv mood. Sorta for the sake of the usage of voucher and a kill time activity. 
Then all of us split up. Some went home, some went to other's hse.
We meet up again late @ nite ard 11pm @ ZOuk. 
It's Party Time!!! Think some of us are high..due to alcohol effect but nvtheless we really have fun.

Like what i've mention in the past article, indeed, I really play as much as I can. My hair still stinks and i can even smell the smoke that is leftover from yesterday night.
But what didnt came true was i did not cry. Thou some indonesian classmates are leaving and will not be back till graduation that day. 
I just sorta know that even if they cannot be present on the last gathering (that will be @ chalet.) , the real last last last time is graduation. 
Till then, it will be our last meeting in sch but not in life i hope...

Sparation, is to be gather 
Gathering, is to be separated

ok i dun really wanna keep on emphasizing but....yeah! im finishing my whole 3 yrs coz of studying tml~!!!! (provided i do not repeat any module~choy!)

It was a really close shave n i almost got myself repeat~
actually i was mix up by the last two ppr...
the last ppr is suppose to be fev and the other is gbv
to think that i have been studying fev the whole day n night juz before the gbv ppr coz i tot that gbv is the last ppr.

lucky i miss out sum lecture notes tt is impt for gbv ppr n asked my classmates for it.
if not i guess i dun haf chance to graduate from poly. 
heng ahz~~~!!! (is really damm heng lo!!!)

I dun wanna go there well prepared with fev and den to my horrify is gbv ppr...
i cfm cry....
in addition to my heng-ness, thinking tt gbv is the last ppr, i actually intend 2 study gbv lastly...i nv touch gbv since the last lecture lehx...diaoz...
double heng-ness lo!!!!! keke.....

well, just had another ppr 2day. Right now, i had finished 2 pprs. 
The feeling is pretty mix-up. Wish so much to finish the last 2 quickly but on the other hand, dun really wanna graduate too soon. Kinda contradicting~~

Im just not used to the feeling of having to work, and probably tis time round, have to work whole lifetime. 
What to do...hai~~~
Right now my plan is finish the exams first and work for a yr or so. Then, probably enroll into NTU, take the coz i wish to take, and hopefully they take in me. 
But, i still dunno wad to work as.......
Maybe sumtink related to the coz i wanna take to enhance my competitive advantage...
hmmmmm~~~~~~~
Good luck to me and to all of you who are having exams~! 
Muacks~~

The Wild Rose
Random Brutal Love Dreamer (RBLDf)


    Colorful, but unpicked. You are The Wild Rose. 

    Prone to bouts of cynicism, sarcasm, and thorns, you excite a certain kind of man. Hoping to gather you up, he flirts and winks and asks you out, ultimately professing his love. Then you make him bleed. Why? Because you're the rare, independent, self-sufficient kind of woman who does want love, but not from a weakling. 

    You don't seem to take yourself too seriously, and that's refreshing. You aren't uptight; you don't over-plan. Romance-wise, sex isn't a top priority--a true relationship would be preferable. For your age, you haven't had a lot of bonafide love experience, though, and this kind of gets to core of the issue. You're very selective. 

    The problem is them, not you, right? You have lofty standards that few measure up to. You're out there all right, but not to be picked up by just anyone. 
 

"You're never truly single as long as you have yourself." 

ALWAYS AVOID: The Bachelor 

CONSIDER: The Vapor Trail.

Natal Year number:  7 
Although Ng may have taken a considerable time to reach maturity, she is nevertheless a quick thinker whose ideas change as rapidly as her conversation.  She's an individual who wants to be liked, and as such finds it hard to refuse requests.  For the same reason she dislikes arguments, and wherever possible will compromise to avoid conflict.  Not the sort of individual to be employed in litigation, but excellent in mediation. 

Natal Month number:  5 
A realist who brings a practical approach to problem solving, Ng's confident outlook will soon lead her to a position of leadership.  Because she has developed fixed views on the important things of life, Ng has an inner core of confidence that will at times make her appear stubborn.  Yet such a trait is so well balanced with the gentle side of her nature, that her personality appeals to a wide audience. 

Natal House number:  7 
Life is likely to provide Ng with many different challenges, but in the end she will overcome the difficulties and make solid progress.  She is prone to talk about subjects on which she has little knowledge, but her communication skills are such that she can be quite persuasive.  She needs to focus on her long-term objectives. 

Comments based on Western Grid
   
 1  
   
 Although Ng may be reasonably talkative in public, she finds it difficult to express personal feelings to those closest to her.  In employment terms, this inhibition is of little consequence. 
   
 2  
   
 Sensitive to criticism and naturally intuitive, Ng has a natural ability to detect insincerity in others.  Because she is a sensitive soul, Ng can be a solid friend and a good listener.  As a result, she will get on well with colleagues, whilst being more than capable of handling office politics. 
   
 44  
   
 A good organiser with creative ability, Ng is inclined to concentrate on pursuits that bring material success, to the exclusion of all else.  She likes to take a project from beginning to end, and will work long and hard to achieve success in her chosen field.  Potentially, there is something of the craftsman in Ng, who could well enjoy the creation of beautiful objects. 
   
 5  
   
 Well-balanced, with an understanding and compassionate nature, Ng is a natural leader who can inspire others.  But she needs a certain amount of freedom at work and at home.  With a compassionate and caring nature, and with the ability to get on well with others, Ng will be a strong member of any team and will provide solid inspiration and support to her colleagues. 
   
 8  
   
 Good with details and with a methodical approach, Ng nevertheless is someone who enjoys constant new challenges to maintain her interest.  She is a methodical individual with attention to detail, but is inclined to leave tasks unfinished if her active mind alights on something of greater interest.  Routine tasks that fail to challenge her intellect are at greatest risk, so Ng needs a job that offers variety. 
   
 9  
   
 Ambitious to improve her lot, Ng will constantly push forward to achieve something in her life, yet this ambition will be balanced by humanitarian ideals that will lead her to support causes that may demand self-sacrifice. 
 [The Arrow of Determination: the numbers 1, 5 and 9]  Determined and persistent, Ng has the patience to wait until she has achieved her goal.  She enjoys a progressive and enterpreneurial approach, and as such, will be an asset to any employer.  If the number 4 (in the Western Grid) is missing, she will be inclined to lose her temper on occasions. 
 [The Arrow of Emotional Balance: the numbers 2, 5 and 8]   Understanding and compassionate, Ng is well-balanced.  She possesses sound leadership qualities that are of use in a wide variety of jobs.  With an understanding and compassionate nature, Ng can appreciate the views of others, and thus gain the respect of the community in which she lives or works. 

Comments based on Chinese Grid
   
 1  
   
 Ng will make some money and enjoy a reasonable standard of living. 
   
 2  
   
 Ng has an average mind, and without the numbers 4 and 9 in the Chinese version will not enjoy a creative existence. 
   
 444  
   
 Very stubborn, and thus unadaptable, Ng finds it difficult to get on with others, and in particular, with those who she believes are less intelligent than her. 
   
 8  
   
 In the absence (in the Chinese version) of the numbers 1 and 6, she will be good with money and details.  She will be happier if the Chinese grid includes the numbers 5 and 7. 
   
 9  
   
 Although Ng is ambitious, her ambition is tempered with humanitarian ideals. 
 [The Arrow of Intellect: The numbers 2, 4 and 9]   Ng is intelligent, articulate and enjoys a first-class memory.  She has a logical and analytical approach that suits her to the legal, medical or accountancy professions. 
 [The Arrow of Loneliness: Lacking the numbers 3, 5 and 7]   Ng is so determined to achieve her objectives that she does so at the expense of all else, including friends, family, love and laughter.

Almost whole of the entreprenuership students will be goin. Ard 50-60 students plus 2-3 lecturers. 
The whole trip cost $165, plus a t-shirt(I hope).
Ok, let's take a look @ the places tt we're goin n c whether wu hua onot.

1st day
Genting
Will be taking cable car and staying @ the New World Hotel(lorkok place)for 1 nite.

2nd day
KL
Staying @ the Capital hotel(is 3-Star man, shld i say wad the hell or better than nothing?)

Last day
Melacca
8pm home sweet home

Most of the time during the day, we'll be on visits.
BUT, it seems like we'll be having much more R&R (rest and relax)time which they would like us to call it as "cultural explosure".
I tink i'll be changing abt S$100 and bring S$20 or sumtink 4 tis trip coz the shopping hrs are not reali short.
So wad? Sch trip or fun-ing? 
Guess both of it. 
Wu hua bo?

Diaoz....
